chasing a ghost in my dreams i keep having dreams that i am chasing a ghost in my house i am scared but angry at the same time that this ghost is in my house then just as i am ready to grab the ghost it is gone from time to time the ghost will jump out get right in my face at this point i wake up screaming the ghost that i am always chasing is like a shadow no face i have had this dream probably once a week for the last or months in general ghosts symbolizes aspects of yourself that you fear this may involve a painful memory guilt or some repressed thoughts you may be afraid of death and dying alternatively ghosts are representative of something that is no longer obtainable or within reach it indicates a feeling of disconnection from life and society this dream may be a calling for you to move on and abandon your outdated modes of thinking and behavior Scenes from a Memory The Amber Spyglass Sigmund Freud Knots Landing Dream Dead Like Me Tag Salad Fingers StarCraft: Uprising Clinical depression Paranoia Agent Ghost Breath of Fire III Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Ghosts 'n Goblins Miss Saigon Out-of-body experience EastEnders Richard Rahl Coast to Coast AM Cordelia Chase Spring Heeled Jack Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Prank flash Blood (computer game) Hypnosis Child sexuality Carl Jung Red Vs. Blue episode guide: Season 2 Jon Secada James Hillman Scooby-Doo Hulk (comics) Narcissism Pac-Man Self-harm Shaggy dog story K' Unconscious mind Animism Anxiety Funeral W. Mark Felt Pok__mon Live! Abortion debate Final Fantasy: Unlimited Darth Vader W.I.T.C.H. E. E. Cummings Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix Xiaolin Showdown Counter-Strike Lucid dreaming Traumatic incident reduction Hide and Seek (Stargate Atlantis) Psychoanalysis Bubble Bobble Avenue Q The Time Machine Karen Horney Max Payne 2: The Fall of Max Payne PANICS Sadism and masochism Diving Myers-Briggs Type Indicator Danny Phantom (character) Sadako Yamamura Autism Anatomy of Criticism Necrophil